t have a diff. I need to keep things concise while addressing the user's request to focus on the active class. \\n\\nAlso, I see that the build.gradle file shows many build arguments from previous changes, but we've only modified one line. It might look like we're violating the focus request, but those changes were already there.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring method handles and diffs**\\n\\nI'm working on editing the Multipart line, but now the git diff against HEAD shows an entire block. It seems that HEAD might not include all changes, while previous modifications are uncommitted by the user. I only added one line, so I need to be careful not to revert unrelated changes.\\n\\nNext, I'm considering if a compile failure could be due to MethodHandles.privateLookupIn requiring certain opens. Existing tests compile fine, but I might have to examine the bytecode further. Also, I wonder if I should add fresh classloader initialization, but the user mentioned no coverage for the public path. So many things to keep track of!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reviewing MethodHandles testing**\\n\\nI'm looking at the existing tests for MethodHandles.privateLookupIn. It seems they might be generating reflective metadata from an agent. This agent should be able to see MethodHandles, which is good. I think this will help with the class$ method's metadata requirements. Overall, it appears like everything is moving in the right direction, but I’ll need to keep an eye on how everything interacts as I finalize my adjustments.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Updated `MultipartPostMethodTest` to directly exercise the remaining dynamic-access call site.\n\nChange made:\n- Added `legacyClassLiteralHelperLoadsMultipartPostMethodType()` in:\n  - `tests/src/commons-httpclient/commons-httpclient/3.0/src/test/java/commons_httpclient/commons_httpclient/MultipartPostMethodTest.java`\n\nThe new test uses `MethodHandles.privateLookupIn(...)` to invoke the legacy compiler-generated `class$` helper on `MultipartPostMethod`, which should execute:\n\n```java\nClass.forName(\"org.apache.commons.httpclient.methods.MultipartPostMethod\")\n```\n\nfrom `MultipartPostMethod.class$(...)`, covering the reported remaining call site.\n\nI did not run compilation or tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0b96b2b9da0f3a38016a049d50fb78819c85ad1d856cd76afa\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 712, "output": 561, "cacheRead": 32768, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34041, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778687301560, "responseId": "resp_0b96b2b9da0f3a38016a049d46b044819cb231b4c4ae6b522d"}, "toolResults": []}
